ORLANDO Pirates and Bafana Bafana star, Thembinkosi Lorch case was postponed. Lorch made his second appearance at the Midrand Magistrates Court earlier on Thursday. The National Prosecuting Authority (NPA) Phindi Mjonondwane confirmed in a statement that the reigning PSL’s Footballer of the Season case was postponed to 27 October. “The case against Orlando Pirates football player, Tembinkosi Lorch was postponed to 27 October 2020 for disclosure of the contents of the docket to his legal representative,” the statement said. “Lorch made his second appearance at the Midrand Magistrates Court earlier today facing a charge of assault with intent to cause grievous bodily harm. He is out on R2000 bail.” The 27-year-old was arrested in September.